# Pollendar frontend env. Copy to `.env` (Vite reads `VITE_`-prefixed vars).
# Base path of the NestJS API. Default `/api` is served same-origin via the dev
# proxy (vite.config.ts) so the auth cookie isn't cross-origin in development.
VITE_API_BASE=/api
# Public origin of this SPA — used to build share / invite links (never hard-code localhost).
VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Production: create a `.env.production` (gitignored) that Vite bakes into `dist/` at build time,
# pointing at the prod origins, e.g.:
#   VITE_API_BASE=https://api.pollendar.example/api
#   VITE_APP_URL=https://pollendar.example
# The matching backend prod env (CORS_ORIGINS / APP_URL / COOKIE_*) is documented in README.md.
